dict.string: Diagnostic logs collected may contain information about the location of your Home, the email addresses of users in the Home, and accessories associated with the Home. This information is used to diagnose issues with HomeKit and improve performance.

CoreRoutine Logs contain sensor data and detailed information about your precise locations over the past approximately 8 weeks. They're used to debug issues with location history, monitoring, and suggestions.

CoreRoutine Logs contain sensor data and detailed information about your precise locations over the past approximately 8 weeks. This includes the precise locations of any places you have visited, your trips including when driving, and workout routes. It also includes motion sensor data, wifi fingerprints, workout duration, proximity events with other devices, and more. This data is used to debug issues with location history, monitoring, and suggestions.
In addition to standard Accessory logs, some logs collected may include Heart Rate related health sensitive data and sensor measurements.
Collected logs may include message and chat identifiers, but will not contain message text.
Messages logging includes collection of an extended age of OS logs as well as statistics to help diagnose unread count and Spotlight issues.
Location logs contain current and past device location. Used to debug any performance issues with location/GPS for navigation, workouts, and more.
Location logs contain raw location coordinates and motion sensor data for up to 3 days.

Wi-Fi Logs included in this report may contain personal information about your Wi-Fi connections, including transferred content and nearby Wi-Fi router hardware addresses. It may also contain Bluetooth logs that include sensitive data like phone call history, shared notification content, paired Bluetooth device names, and recently connected or nearby devices. If you're concerned about the included information, you can go back to review or remove it.

WLAN Logs included in this report may contain personal information about your WLAN connections, including transferred content and nearby WLAN router hardware addresses. It may also contain Bluetooth logs that include sensitive data like phone call history, shared notification content, paired Bluetooth device names, and recently connected or nearby devices. If you're concerned about the included information, you can go back to review or remove it.
